    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim exits improperly from sessions involving more than one vim window when `shellslash` is set on MSYS2 for Windows with /usr/bin/bash as the login shell.  As a consequence of improperly exiting, the neovim UI stays in the console scrollback buffer and the console is put in a bizarre state where scrolling is broken.\n\nThe problem happens both on a clean config `-u NONE` and on a config with the following (additional) shell options:\n\n```vim\nset shell=C:/msys64/usr/bin/bash.exe\nset shellcmdflag=-c\nset shellquote=\nset shellxquote=\nset shellredir=>%s\\ 2>&1\nset shellpipe=2>&1\\|\\ tee\n```\n\nI cannot reproduce the problem on WSL Arch Linux.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\npacman --sync mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-neovim\nnvim -u NONE\n:set shellslash\n:help shellslash (any command opening a new vim window would do)\n:qa\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim exits cleanly with a return code 0 and does not leave any traces in the interactive console.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.6\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim v9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal v1.23.20211.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nMSYS2 Package repository",
