            "body": "> Try the latest development version. The [Releases](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/tag/nightly) page has pre-built archives for Linux/Windows/macOS. Check `:version` to confirm the version.\n> \n> May be fixed after [#37729](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37729)\n\nIt seems like the way UCRT64 neovim is packaged and distributed by MSYS2 is different from the official Windows builds. For instance, the UCRT64 uses the .so files in /lib/ instead of .dll so I tried to download both the win and linux nightly builds to get all the files but my installation was bugged, I had a bunch of LSP errors just opening help pages so I am probably doing things wrong.",
